This was *the* burrito place in the Boston-Cambridge area back in the day, especially at this location. I was incredibly disappointed with my meal tonight. My carnitas burrito was greasy, so greasy it leaked through the bag and all over the eating surface. You'd think this was a sign the meat was moist, tender, and tasty? Unfortunately the meat was overly salty, and surprisingly dry considering the grease, with a metallic after taste to it. I am giving it two stars due to nostalgia, due to the fact that the people behind the counter were super nice and its obvious they are part of the new management and just learning the ropes, and because the chips and guac are still outstanding. I tossed the burrito though. A hard pass from me until they fix their issues.

High-quality food and quick counter service make this a convenient and tasty place to stop in for lunch. Prices are good for the quality. This stuff puts Chipotle to shame. They also carry delicious Jarritos Mexican fruit sodas, which are always worth it. Give it a try! They usually have a line out the door around lunch time, so you know people around the area appreciate it!

Dismal experience. Sub-par unenthusiastic service, an inexplicable additional $0.65 charge on the burrito (as a matter of principle - if you advertise your prices as $7 for a burrito [filling + beans etc], no sour cream or guac, then it should be $7 pretax), poorly wrapped to boot - makes for a messy and terrible lunch experience, that's for sure.

The food is amazing , fresh ! They don’t have freezers or microwave , food is prepare every morning! awesome variety of vegan dishes and also different types of meat ! Great portion ! Much more Tex than Mex. As a Mexican expecting something resembling what I’ve had at other restaurants, the food was severely lacking. Tacos were extremely fragile and the meat used was humongous cubes of 50% fat 50% beef. Family ordered a quesadilla and was given something that resembled more of a burrito. Had to give our order to the cashier only to repeat the order 2 minutes later to the cook. Upon inspection after finishing, we were charged extra for sour cream and guacamole when we never got any.  For anyone searching for Mexican food this establishment does not have it.

This is a great little restaurant, popular for lunch with the many techies who work in the area. It's kind of like a more-authentic version of Qdoba = choose the meal type (salad, burritos, tacos, etc.), pick the fillings, and watch it get made -- but, the food is infinitely better than any national chain. Gets really busy during the noon hour, but service is fast. There is seating available on the second floor.
